headline: Chime debut, ConAgra downgrade, Cardinal Health lifts outlook
summary: Yahoo Finance host Josh Lipton tracks today's top moving stocks and biggest market stories in this Market Minute. Chime (CHYM) debuts on the Nasdaq Composite (^IXIC), opening at $43 per share. ConAgra Brands (CAG) was downgraded to Underperform from Neutral by BofA Securities and lowered its price target to $20 from $27. Cardinal Health (CAH) stock is rising after lifting its earnings outlook for the full year. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: Conagra Brands Stock Falls After Downgrade. Rising Meat Prices Are to Blame.
summary: Conagra Brands  stock was down Thursday after analysts at BofA Securities reduced their outlook for the packaged food maker, citing the rising cost of meat.  Peter T. Galbo and Yasmine Deswandhy at BofA downgraded  Conagra  stock to Underperform from Neutral and lowered their price target to $20 from $27 in a research note Thursday.  Conagra, which owns brands like Slim Jim, Chef Boyardee, and Hebrew National, could see its product expenses climb considerably in fiscal 2026, the analysts said.

headline: BofA cuts ConAgra Brands, says ’protein-flation to take bite out of FY26 earnings’
summary: Investing.com -- Bank of America lowered its rating for ConAgra Brands to Underperform from Neutral in a note Thursday, lowering its price target for the stock to $20 from $27 a share.
